%N A395674 Odd powerful numbers that are not powers of squarefree numbers.
%C A395674 Intersection of A005408 and A359280, where the latter sequence is A001694 \ A072777.
%C A395674 Smallest term with k distinct prime factors is 3*A061742(k)/4 = 3*A070826(k)^2 = 3/4*A002110(k)^2, with k > 2.
%H A395674 Michael De Vlieger, <a href="/A395674/b395674.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%e A395674 Table of n, a(n) for select n:
%e A395674      n        a(n)
%e A395674 -------------------------------------------------
%e A395674      1         675 = 3^3 * 5^2
%e A395674      2        1125 = 3^2 * 5^3
%e A395674      3        1323 = 3^3 * 7^2
%e A395674      4        2025 = 3^4 * 5^2
%e A395674      5        3087 = 3^2 * 7^3
%e A395674      6        3267 = 3^3 * 11^2
%e A395674      7        3969 = 3^4 * 7^2
%e A395674      8        4563 = 3^3 * 13^2
%e A395674      9        5625 = 3^2 * 5^4
%e A395674     36       33075 = 3^3 * 5^2 * 7^2
%e A395674    629     4002075 = 3^3 * 5^2 * 7^2 * 11^2
%e A395674   9531   676350675 = 3^3 * 5^2 * 7^2 * 11^2 * 13^2
%t A395674 Select[Range[1, 40000, 2], (powers = FactorInteger[#][[All, -1]]; And[AllTrue[powers, # > 1 &], CountDistinct[powers] > 1]) &]
